Job Description:
A SF Bay Area medical device company is seeking an Analytical scientist for the molecular spectroscopy analysis position. Candidates involved in spectroscopic data analysis on tissue spectroscopic measurements are most desired for efforts related to development of novel medical devices. The successful candidate will have the opportunity to be deeply involved in the science, development, and data analysis of a new generation of medical devices based on spectroscopic technologies. Full time position is available.
Responsibilities
Responsibilities include: spectral data extractions, spectroscopic data modeling, and spectra analysis; algorithm development; assist to providing feedback to modify and optimize spectroscopy experiments; provide data analysis and data-based guidance on spectroscopic experimental setup;

I: Essential Job Functions:
Responsible for designing, developing, testing, and refining the statistical algorithms used to power the worlds leading Data Management Platform, the Lotame DMP;
Apply experience in data modeling, data mining and optimization to very large scale data sets, producing solutions to meet the ever-changing demands of Lotames fast growing product suite;
Work directly with Lotames Chief Data Scientist to provide statistical algorithm development and support to a variety of products, including Lotames Optimizer and Cross Device;
Work with Product Managers, Data Engineers, and Software Developers to tackle a variety of complex problems, and as a part of this team delivers scalable, efficient solutions to our customers.


